I have a custom class as follows:

[code]
# MyClass.gd

class MyClass:

vars ...

func _init(arg1, arg2, arg3):
       print(arg1)
func otherFunc():
       #do stuff
[/code]

MyClass.gd gets loaded by a script attached to PopupWindow:
[code]
extends PopupDialog

vars ...
var MyClass = preload("res://Scripts/MyClass.gd")

func _ready():
       var MyClassInst = MyClass.new("hi", "I dont", "work")
       MyClassInst.otherFunc() #Debugger says it doesn't exist
[/code]

The result is Godot crashes and never even loads the popup window. There is no error in the Godot debug console. If I don't create a new MyClass script everything works fine. Is this a bug in loading classes?
